The paper deals with MAP estimation in graphical models, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of Lagrangian relaxation techniques is a popular approach in optimization, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also mentions dynamic programming techniques, which are commonly used in algorithms for discrete optimization problems, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper also deals with optimization on graphs, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
